	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">We usually fill the entire chip to reduce the chances for errors when soldering the chip, because even if you don't ground all the upper address pins the game will still work. If you have full confidence in your soldering, there's no need to fill the chip.</div>
<br />
<br />Not so much about soldering (as a floating line can cause all sorts of glitches even with duplicated data) as it is to have it work even if you tie one line high/low when it should've been vice versa.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


